  "timeboxMinutes": 30,
  "prompt": "Accounting needs to match uploaded receipts to card transactions.\n\nWrite `match_receipts_to_transactions(base_url, token)`. Fetch all transactions and all receipts, then return a mapping from transaction id to receipt id.\n\nA receipt can match a transaction when:\n\n- same `employee_id`\n- same non-null `amount_cents`\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `dict[str, str]`, shaped like `{\"txn_001\": \"rcp_001\"}`.\n- Keys are transaction ids. Values are receipt ids.\n- Skip receipts whose `amount_cents` is `None`.\n- If multiple transactions have the same match key, assign receipts to unmatched transactions in transaction API order.\n- If extra receipts remain after all matching transactions are assigned, ignore the extras.\n- If there are no matches, return `{}`.\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET /v1/transactions` and `GET /v1/receipts` are both paginated and require auth.\n- Both use `{\"data\": [...], \"next_cursor\": \"...\" | None}`.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- Fetch every page from both endpoints.\n- Do not match null receipt amounts.\n- Do not match only on amount; employee id must also match.\n- Do not assign the same transaction twice.\n- A hash map keyed by `(employee_id, amount_cents)` is the natural shape.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: complete pagination on both endpoints, null handling, duplicate amounts, same-employee matching, and deterministic one-to-one assignment.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "matchReceiptsToTransactions",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
